answers.answer: Protein in urine is a sign of pre eclampsia even with normal blood pressure.
It could also be a UTI also kidney damage.  And anything lower than 80 is normal.

question: Does anyone know anything about protein in urine and at what level its considered high...I dida 24 hr test and my level was 154...i had preeclampsia with my first baby and thus is baby number 4...I have had some swelling in my feet and some dizziness...my b.p is good....any advice?
